1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:08,050 --> 00:00:09,750
Good afternoon, Marcelka.

3
00:00:10,550 --> 00:00:12,040
So, how did it go today?

4
00:00:12,350 --> 00:00:14,160
Fine, except for Ozzak's tardiness.

5
00:00:14,350 --> 00:00:17,200
Well, you know Ozzak, half an hour here, half an hour there.

6
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:19,380
This time it's 7 hours and 34 minutes.

7
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:21,740
Wow, a new record.

8
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:24,380
Did you forget those 14 days back in March?

9
00:00:24,850 --> 00:00:27,350
Well, the Jezevec had premium lager days.

10
00:00:27,660 --> 00:00:30,120
Tomas, good that you're here, I'm in a terrible rush.

11
00:00:30,120 --> 00:00:35,250
Could you stay here until closing, I need to get changed, otherwise I won't make it.

12
00:00:35,550 --> 00:00:39,440
Zoran is taking me to an important Croatian social event today.

13
00:00:41,450 --> 00:00:43,680
Yeah, but I already promised Iva we'd go to the movies today.

14
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:44,220
What's playing?

15
00:00:45,150 --> 00:00:49,520
Some quality film, so it'll be four hours long and not much talking.

16
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:50,600
I envy you.

17
00:00:50,650 --> 00:00:52,850
I couldn't get Zoran to a movie theater.

18
00:00:53,250 --> 00:00:54,940
He's always at work.

19
00:00:55,250 --> 00:00:58,150
He only takes me out when Hajduk Split is playing in Prague.

20
00:01:01,420 --> 00:01:03,780
Right, they're actually playing Sparta today.

21
00:01:03,780 --> 00:01:08,000
I last saw Zoran in July when Hajduk played Banik.

22
00:01:08,450 --> 00:01:10,550
And when they win, Zoran's in great form.

23
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:15,560
Don't get your hopes up, Sparta's in great form too.

24
00:01:15,780 --> 00:01:17,540
Don't worry, Zoran sponsors them.

25
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:18,220
Hajduk?

26
00:01:18,300 --> 00:01:18,620
Sparta.

27
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:19,700
I have to run.

28
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:21,200
Of course.

29
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:27,020
Well, Ivushka will have to understand, but it's fine, I'll just watch the Hajduk Split game on TV at home tonight.

30
00:01:27,020 --> 00:01:27,660
You're a sweetheart.

31
00:01:30,370 --> 00:01:31,370
Bye, girls.

32
00:01:31,650 --> 00:01:31,990
Bye.

33
00:01:35,650 --> 00:01:37,950
Father, where are you going again?

34
00:01:38,650 --> 00:01:42,350
Ozzak still hasn't shown up, so I have to stay here until closing.

35
00:01:43,150 --> 00:01:46,250
I'm really sorry, girls, I was really looking forward to it.

36
00:01:46,450 --> 00:01:47,150
No way.

37
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:52,380
I won't let you embarrass us at the parent-teacher meeting again, like when you refused to pay 120 crowns for The Big Feast.

38
00:01:52,620 --> 00:01:54,260
How was I supposed to know it was a movie?

39
00:01:54,380 --> 00:01:56,320
Everyone knows that, unless they're a cultural primitive.

40
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,520
Old Voracek didn't know either.

41
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:01,820
Yeah, but at least he kept quiet and didn't yell "then what are we paying for lunches for?"

42
00:02:03,050 --> 00:02:04,050
And what about the shop?

43
00:02:04,450 --> 00:02:05,840
I already woke Ozzak up.

44
00:02:05,950 --> 00:02:07,050
He'll be here any minute.

45
00:02:08,050 --> 00:02:10,250
You were watching teleshopping all night again.

46
00:02:10,850 --> 00:02:13,450
Sorry, bro, but those new TV shopping shows are pretty gripping.

47
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:17,440
I had to wait and see if someone bought the mole repeller.

48
00:02:18,220 --> 00:02:21,620
Tomorrow you're opening the shop, even if I have to drag you out of bed myself.

49
00:02:22,950 --> 00:02:24,240
So what are we actually going to see?

50
00:02:24,550 --> 00:02:25,550
All About My Mother.

51
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:27,750
Uncle, don't you want to come with us?

52
00:02:27,950 --> 00:02:29,530
Thanks, I appreciate everything.

53
00:02:29,530 --> 00:02:30,250
Let Lexa go.

54
00:02:30,850 --> 00:02:31,710
Why can't he?

55
00:02:31,850 --> 00:02:32,710
I don't blame him.

56
00:02:32,710 --> 00:02:33,850
Knowing everything about a mother.

57
00:02:33,910 --> 00:02:35,030
Not even if they paid me.

58
00:02:35,230 --> 00:02:36,790
But it's not about Simona, Uncle.

59
00:02:37,450 --> 00:02:40,050
Going to movies about someone else's mother seems totally nuts.

60
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:42,350
Jesus, you're an even bigger barbarian than Dad.

61
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:44,190
Have you even seen Empties?

62
00:02:44,550 --> 00:02:45,350
I see those every day.

63
00:02:46,550 --> 00:02:50,250
The only thing he wanted to see was Kamenak, because he thought it'd be about the Stones.

64
00:02:50,250 --> 00:02:51,530
It gets even worse.

65
00:02:52,050 --> 00:02:53,650
Yeah, disgusting stuff.

66
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:55,750
Has he ever even seen a normal film?

67
00:02:56,010 --> 00:02:56,870
Hmm, once.

68
00:02:57,070 --> 00:02:58,230
The Mummy Returns.

69
00:03:05,950 --> 00:03:06,750
How did you know?

70
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:36,950
Are they gone yet?

71
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:42,150
First they wanted to see a movie about Simona and then they picked a complete stranger's mother.

72
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:45,590
So nobody's home at your place now?

73
00:03:45,590 --> 00:03:46,350
Nope.

74
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:51,050
Want to go bowling again with empty beer bottles?

75
00:03:51,450 --> 00:03:52,990
No, I've got something better.

76
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:54,050
Full bottles.

77
00:03:54,350 --> 00:03:55,550
Even better than that.

78
00:03:55,850 --> 00:03:58,450
I got this special film.

79
00:03:59,550 --> 00:04:00,650
Movies bore me.

80
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:05,180
I mean, you nap for an hour or wait in line for beer and come back, and you've lost the plot.

81
00:04:05,550 --> 00:04:07,180
But this is a totally different kind of movie, it's...

82
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:08,260
It's...

83
00:04:08,260 --> 00:04:08,750
An adult film?

84
00:04:13,150 --> 00:04:14,540
You know those kinds of movies?

85
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:18,550
Not much plot, lots of girls, not much clothing?

86
00:04:18,990 --> 00:04:19,470
What?

87
00:04:20,850 --> 00:04:21,350
This?

88
00:04:21,850 --> 00:04:23,050
Lexa, are you crazy?

89
00:04:23,650 --> 00:04:26,960
Don't you know these movies cause deafness and dry up your spinal fluid?

90
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:28,900
My grandma used to say that too, Uncle.

91
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:35,350
But this is Barunka's Garden, and it's got that legendary love scene in Grandmother's Valley.

92
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:40,290
If Voracek sees it before me, I'll be the last person at the Jezevec who hasn't seen it.

93
00:04:40,290 --> 00:04:40,690
Right.

94
00:04:41,150 --> 00:04:42,950
Fine, I'll watch with you as a chaperone.

95
00:04:43,550 --> 00:04:46,050
But if I see your spinal fluid drying up, I'm turning it off.

96
00:04:47,150 --> 00:04:48,250
I'll go get it then.

97
00:04:49,050 --> 00:04:51,350
I've got it hidden in a secret spot.

98
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:56,970
Can I borrow the keys to your cellar?

99
00:04:59,150 --> 00:05:09,570
So, miss, where is it, let me take a look at it?

100
00:05:09,570 --> 00:05:11,430
Go ahead, spread it open.

101
00:05:12,150 --> 00:05:13,450
Well, I wouldn't have expected that.

102
00:05:14,850 --> 00:05:16,250
Ah, right here.

103
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:19,550
Excuse me, my dress fell off.

104
00:05:19,650 --> 00:05:22,250
Well, I'll start with you then.

105
00:05:23,450 --> 00:05:24,450
Fast-forward this.

106
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:27,050
I want to know if he fixes the TV.

107
00:05:27,550 --> 00:05:28,650
I bet it's the cable.

108
00:05:29,550 --> 00:05:30,950
That's a long one though.

109
00:05:32,650 --> 00:05:34,450
Lexa, you don't like this?

110
00:05:35,450 --> 00:05:36,350
What do you think of it?

111
00:05:36,650 --> 00:05:37,770
It's like with booze.

112
00:05:38,050 --> 00:05:39,750
If I'm not doing it myself, it's no fun.

113
00:05:40,150 --> 00:05:42,250
Yeah, but nobody will serve me yet.

114
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,350
I get it.

115
00:05:44,150 --> 00:05:45,450
I was eleven once too.

116
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:50,050
And right after the miller left her, the dark huntsman arrived.

117
00:05:53,710 --> 00:05:56,010
Mr. Ozzak, come, come, the Grandmother's Valley scene is on now.

118
00:05:56,450 --> 00:05:59,750
Yes, in the cottage it's always lively.

119
00:05:59,970 --> 00:06:00,450
Awesome.

120
00:06:02,550 --> 00:06:03,740
Sultan, make room.

121
00:06:04,050 --> 00:06:04,450
Woof, woof.

122
00:06:04,450 --> 00:06:06,250
Good doggy.

123
00:06:07,930 --> 00:06:08,410
Mom?

124
00:06:09,330 --> 00:06:17,810
Hey girls, thanks for taking me along.

125
00:06:18,050 --> 00:06:19,290
All About My Mother.

126
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:22,650
Who would have thought it'd be so interesting?

127
00:06:22,850 --> 00:06:23,650
Hi.

128
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:26,020
Too bad you guys couldn't see it too.

129
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:30,750
Ozzak, guess what, the main character's father was a woman.

130
00:06:30,770 --> 00:06:31,970
I really didn't see that coming.

131
00:06:31,970 --> 00:06:33,850
See, and you didn't even want to go, right?

132
00:06:34,010 --> 00:06:38,390
They showed beautifully how having a family secret can destroy a person.

133
00:06:38,730 --> 00:06:42,830
How important it is to communicate and not bottle up your feelings, right?

134
00:06:42,910 --> 00:06:43,470
What?

135
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:45,150
And you'll definitely have an edge over old Voracek now.

136
00:06:48,030 --> 00:06:50,030
He'll be stunned at the parent-teacher meeting.

137
00:06:51,150 --> 00:06:56,650
I'm just not sure, girls, whether some scenes weren't too risque.

138
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:58,550
Well...

139
00:06:58,650 --> 00:07:01,750
We didn't even hear the risque scenes anyway, right?

140
00:07:02,180 --> 00:07:02,680
Sorry.

141
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,650
Why do you do that?

142
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:07,310
Plug your ears and sing.

143
00:07:07,650 --> 00:07:09,610
We're lucky they didn't kick us out.

144
00:07:09,610 --> 00:07:10,530
It's a reflex.

145
00:07:11,350 --> 00:07:13,950
If you had Lexa for a brother.

146
00:07:17,850 --> 00:07:18,550
Yeah, yeah.

147
00:07:18,950 --> 00:07:21,750
Movies can really awaken emotions in a person.

148
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:24,590
See, Lexa, this is much better than your disgusting stuff.

149
00:07:24,590 --> 00:07:24,810
Yeah.

150
00:07:24,930 --> 00:07:26,450
What disgusting stuff?

151
00:07:28,350 --> 00:07:29,150
What's wrong, Lexa?

152
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:31,150
We have a problem.

153
00:07:32,350 --> 00:07:33,850
I didn't want to tell you, but...

154
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,750
Lexa's spinal fluid has probably dried up.

155
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:38,950
I was just about to start treating him.

156
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:43,510
Ozzak, what happened here?

157
00:07:43,650 --> 00:07:45,350
I honestly have no idea.

158
00:07:46,050 --> 00:07:47,310
Lexa, what's wrong?

159
00:07:47,310 --> 00:07:50,110
Maybe it'd help if he also expressed his feelings.

160
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:52,250
He should also see All About My Mother.

161
00:07:52,490 --> 00:07:54,150
No, no, no, please, not that again!

162
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:56,750
Lexa!

163
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:57,640
Sasha!

164
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:04,000
Ozzak, please, can you explain what's going on here, what happened?

165
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,700
His spinal fluid hasn't dried up, well that's great!

166
00:08:06,940 --> 00:08:08,060
What were you doing here?

167
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,540
We were watching a movie too.

168
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:14,340
And given that Lexa is running and talking, I'd say it was a pretty successful cultural evening.

169
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:15,800
You were watching a movie?

170
00:08:16,020 --> 00:08:16,360
Yeah.

171
00:08:17,150 --> 00:08:19,260
I finally saw the kind that aren't complicated.

172
00:08:19,450 --> 00:08:21,500
Great, so next time you can go with Dad.

173
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,400
Or we could rent something.

174
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:25,280
I'd rather pop down to the cellar.

175
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,460
Well, in any case...

176
00:08:38,450 --> 00:08:40,250
Maybe we'll have to stay here forever.

177
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:42,940
They'll hardly find us on this deserted island.

178
00:08:43,820 --> 00:08:46,420
Yes, just the two of us and my ten girlfriends.

179
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:47,880
And we only brought two bikinis.

180
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:48,960
What is this?

181
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,860
We'll try to start a new tribe here.

182
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:56,980
A new tribe.

183
00:08:58,150 --> 00:08:59,150
That never would've occurred to me.

184
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:01,750
Well, excellent.

185
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:15,850
I didn't expect you'd be up and about this early.

186
00:09:16,850 --> 00:09:19,740
But bro, we shouldn't be afraid to express our feelings.

187
00:09:21,550 --> 00:09:24,550
So I commend you for taking getting up for work so seriously.

188
00:09:25,350 --> 00:09:27,850
Yeah, thanks.

189
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:30,360
Now I'm going to lie down because I'm completely dead.

190
00:09:30,850 --> 00:09:34,150
No, no, no, no, don't try that on me.

191
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:36,150
That's not happening.

192
00:09:36,950 --> 00:09:38,850
You're opening the shop and that's that.

193
00:10:38,150 --> 00:10:39,550
So, Ozzak, you two aren't speaking?

194
00:10:43,050 --> 00:10:44,050
Because of last night?

195
00:10:46,450 --> 00:10:47,550
Maybe it wasn't her?

196
00:10:48,350 --> 00:10:53,850
It could've been some woman who looks exactly the same as Mom.

197
00:10:55,950 --> 00:10:56,950
That's stupid, isn't it?

198
00:10:57,930 --> 00:10:58,730
Never mind.

199
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:00,740
Thanks then.

200
00:11:02,020 --> 00:11:02,620
Bye.

201
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:09,820
Hello.

202
00:11:11,650 --> 00:11:13,040
Why so glum, Lexa?

203
00:11:13,450 --> 00:11:14,950
Because of last night.

204
00:11:15,060 --> 00:11:16,800
You saw that horror too?

205
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,820
Of course, Zoran too.

206
00:11:19,150 --> 00:11:21,900
Didn't see much of it, but all of Prague did.

207
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:23,850
So even Voracek already knows.

208
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:32,780
See, Mr. Ozzak, it is possible.

209
00:11:33,180 --> 00:11:34,600
Getting up for work in the morning.

210
00:11:45,350 --> 00:11:47,290
And I had to chant along with everyone else.

211
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:50,950
My throat still hurts today and it was all for nothing.

212
00:11:51,150 --> 00:11:55,340
Hajduk lost, Zoran was furious and was ripping up chunks of turf.

213
00:11:55,650 --> 00:11:59,150
Now he's lying at home on the Croatian flag, crying.

214
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:02,230
You're like a different person today.

215
00:12:02,450 --> 00:12:04,930
It's been ages since I had such a nice chat with you.

216
00:12:04,930 --> 00:12:06,430
Did something happen to you yesterday?

217
00:12:07,450 --> 00:12:09,050
I watched movies.

218
00:12:09,450 --> 00:12:12,850
I thought movies weren't exactly your cup of beer.

219
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:20,480
Ah.

220
00:12:41,050 --> 00:12:43,850
Although there were certain scenes I had to fast-forward through.

221
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:44,820
Classic Bergman.

222
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,360
I had no idea, my God, you're interested in this too?

223
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:48,800
I've got a whole bunch here.

224
00:12:50,350 --> 00:12:51,550
Everyone lent me something yesterday.

225
00:12:51,850 --> 00:12:52,850
Show me.

226
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:56,400
This is wonderful, all Bergman.

227
00:12:56,450 --> 00:12:59,300
I don't even know some of these titles, like Deep Throat.

228
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:00,300
And that one's really outstanding.

229
00:13:01,050 --> 00:13:03,620
But your friend isn't very careful.

230
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:08,050
Such a beautiful collection and so many errors in the titles, like here.

231
00:13:08,250 --> 00:13:11,190
Fanny and Alexander instead of Fanny and Alexander.

232
00:13:11,550 --> 00:13:14,850
Or here, instead of Cries and Whispers it says Whispers and Squirts.

233
00:13:14,850 --> 00:13:16,310
That sounds like it's about firefighters.

234
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:18,290
Is it about firefighters?

235
00:13:18,290 --> 00:13:22,850
Mr. Ozzak, could you lend me something to watch at home, maybe those Whispers?

236
00:13:23,050 --> 00:13:24,910
Sure, no problem, folks, I've already seen it anyway.

237
00:13:25,130 --> 00:13:27,610
I'll try to convince Zoran to watch it with me.

238
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:29,210
Maybe it'll cheer him up.

239
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:30,250
I'd believe that.

240
00:13:30,470 --> 00:13:32,490
But watch out for the dried-up spinal fluid.

241
00:14:07,450 --> 00:14:09,550
Damn it, I'm all splashed, I had no idea.

242
00:14:14,250 --> 00:14:15,550
Hello, miss.

243
00:14:15,780 --> 00:14:17,400
So where do you have it?

244
00:14:17,460 --> 00:14:18,460
What should I look at?

245
00:14:25,810 --> 00:14:26,250
Marcelka!

246
00:14:27,130 --> 00:14:28,570
So how was last night?

247
00:14:28,570 --> 00:14:31,750
How did Zoran handle getting thrashed by Madera?

248
00:14:31,950 --> 00:14:32,730
He didn't.

249
00:14:32,950 --> 00:14:35,650
He acted like you when we lost to Turkey.

250
00:14:36,350 --> 00:14:37,450
Turf and flag?

251
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:40,720
But you're in a great mood today.

252
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:41,980
It's the movie from yesterday.

253
00:14:41,980 --> 00:14:44,650
I have no idea why I stopped going to the movies.

254
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:46,350
It completely captivated me.

255
00:14:46,540 --> 00:14:49,200
I wanted to ask, would you like to go sometime too?

256
00:14:49,340 --> 00:14:51,960
But you'll probably have to comfort Zoran, right?

257
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:55,620
Well, fortunately your brother lent me a quality film to take home.

258
00:14:56,740 --> 00:14:57,340
Ozzak?

259
00:14:58,550 --> 00:15:01,750
He never even finished How the Mole Got His Trousers.

260
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:05,350
Hold on, I may have actually seen something like that.

261
00:15:05,950 --> 00:15:08,460
Bro, are you confusing it with teleshopping?

262
00:15:08,650 --> 00:15:09,350
You think?

263
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:12,860
Tomas, don't underestimate your brother.

264
00:15:12,860 --> 00:15:14,380
We've already been discussing this here.

265
00:15:14,420 --> 00:15:16,180
Ozzak watches Bergman at night.

266
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:20,250
My brother Ozzak?

267
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:23,000
Clearly you don't know everything about your brother.

268
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,930
And why didn't you ever hint at this to me?

269
00:15:25,990 --> 00:15:27,630
We could've gone to the movies together.

270
00:15:29,250 --> 00:15:30,530
Hey, I'm going to see Sex and the City today.

271
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:34,230
That's probably too commercial for a Bergman admirer.

272
00:15:34,290 --> 00:15:35,670
Of course, plus I've already seen it.

273
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:37,610
Even the sequels set in the countryside.

274
00:15:37,850 --> 00:15:39,890
Maybe you could even learn from him.

275
00:15:39,970 --> 00:15:42,150
Perhaps he'll lend you something from his collection?

276
00:15:43,150 --> 00:15:44,250
I...

277
00:15:44,450 --> 00:15:48,050
I usually fall asleep during art films.

278
00:15:48,230 --> 00:15:49,330
A barbarian and an ignoramus.

279
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:52,890
Your brother and I prefer higher-quality productions.

280
00:15:52,950 --> 00:15:57,670
No unnecessary talking, emotions expressed through body language, humanity laid completely bare.

281
00:15:58,350 --> 00:15:59,190
Practically the whole time.

282
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:00,550
Completely bare.

283
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:02,830
Hey, Ivushka.

284
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:03,470
Hi.

285
00:16:03,490 --> 00:16:04,950
So, are we going to the movies again?

286
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:06,790
Ivushka, today I'm going alone.

287
00:16:06,910 --> 00:16:09,290
It's too commercial, you know, Sex and the City.

288
00:16:09,950 --> 00:16:11,250
But we want to see it too.

289
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:13,190
Absolutely not, plus it's restricted.

290
00:16:13,430 --> 00:16:14,010
It isn't.

291
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:15,060
And it should be.

292
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,860
As a parent, I need to see it first.

293
00:16:17,450 --> 00:16:19,050
You can read magazines with Sasha.

294
00:16:20,140 --> 00:16:21,800
You unexpectedly get invited to a party.

295
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:22,760
What do you wear?

296
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:25,720
A: Something cool and comfortable.

297
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:28,520
B: Lexa, where have you been all day?

298
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:31,350
If Mom notices that stuff, you're in big trouble.

299
00:16:32,350 --> 00:16:33,470
Lend me the keys to the attic.

300
00:16:33,850 --> 00:16:34,650
Sure.

301
00:16:34,850 --> 00:16:36,850
I dry my panties in the bathroom anyway.

302
00:16:39,250 --> 00:16:40,350
They're on the rack.

303
00:16:40,820 --> 00:16:42,120
Lexa, you have to sleep in the attic?

304
00:16:42,220 --> 00:16:44,140
You were using Mom's razor again.

305
00:16:45,450 --> 00:16:46,250
No, nothing happened.

306
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:48,950
It's just too hot at home.

307
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:50,430
Then open a window.

308
00:16:50,650 --> 00:16:52,850
No, I can't, because then it'd be too cold.

309
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:55,950
Lexa, you're weirder than usual.

310
00:16:56,450 --> 00:16:57,620
Did something happen to you?

311
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:58,660
No, nothing happened.

312
00:16:58,850 --> 00:17:00,050
What would happen?

313
00:17:00,450 --> 00:17:07,650
I just didn't go to school, wandered along the river, and now I'm going to sleep in the attic.

314
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:16,930
Sasha, remember how I used to prank-call that hotline and pretend I wanted to commit suicide?

315
00:17:16,930 --> 00:17:17,250
Yeah.

316
00:17:17,950 --> 00:17:19,250
Do you remember the number?

317
00:17:19,370 --> 00:17:19,850
No.

318
00:17:21,150 --> 00:17:26,950
Lexa, wait, I don't like saying this and I may regret it, but do you want to talk to us?

319
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:35,950
I watched porn.

320
00:17:36,450 --> 00:17:37,750
Go to the attic.

321
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:41,290
I'll try to find that number, maybe someone there will listen to me.

322
00:17:41,550 --> 00:17:43,850
No, wait, just wait.

323
00:17:44,950 --> 00:17:48,250
Was there a guy in it that you liked?

324
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:50,350
There was a guy dressed as a dog.

325
00:17:50,350 --> 00:17:51,210
Go to the attic.

326
00:17:51,210 --> 00:17:52,650
And there was a woman.

327
00:17:53,350 --> 00:17:55,650
And that woman was our mom.

328
00:17:57,450 --> 00:17:59,550
Lexa, how can you say that?

329
00:17:59,650 --> 00:18:00,870
Sasha, don't be ridiculous.

330
00:18:01,150 --> 00:18:02,090
You know Lexa.

331
00:18:02,450 --> 00:18:03,510
God knows what he saw.

332
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:05,550
See for yourself then.

333
00:18:07,850 --> 00:18:08,750
Give it here.

334
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,820
Want to see what's in my tool belt?

335
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:14,560
Woof, woof, woof.

336
00:18:21,050 --> 00:18:22,860
I just don't get it.

337
00:18:22,860 --> 00:18:24,720
How can guys watch this stuff?

338
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:27,850
These women are like pieces of meat.

339
00:18:27,950 --> 00:18:30,550
Don't talk about my mom like that.

340
00:18:31,650 --> 00:18:32,250
Sorry.

341
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:34,400
Now here it comes.

342
00:18:35,350 --> 00:18:48,750
Iva, what is the meaning of this?

343
00:18:49,610 --> 00:18:51,310
But this isn't at all what you think.

344
00:18:51,370 --> 00:18:52,750
Oh sure, it's completely different, right?

345
00:18:52,930 --> 00:18:56,190
My own daughter is here watching porn with the gang from next door.

346
00:18:57,650 --> 00:19:00,150
And Sasha, you're singing along for him?

347
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:07,350
That guy is literally dressed as a dog.

348
00:19:09,870 --> 00:19:10,370
Simona!

349
00:19:15,650 --> 00:19:19,850
Oh, so you're watching Bergman too, huh?

350
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:21,920
Don't joke around.

351
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:23,350
This is serious.

352
00:19:25,850 --> 00:19:28,850
How are these poor kids going to look their own mother in the eye now?

353
00:19:29,350 --> 00:19:30,830
You shouldn't have shown it to them then.

354
00:19:30,850 --> 00:19:32,550
Bergman isn't for kids.

355
00:19:33,150 --> 00:19:34,050
Hi there.

356
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:37,250
So, kids, where are you?

357
00:19:37,550 --> 00:19:40,250
I come home in the evening and two important things are missing.

358
00:19:40,950 --> 00:19:42,150
A sleeping bag and an alarm clock.

359
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:44,610
I got held up at work.

360
00:19:44,950 --> 00:19:48,350
I was starting to think the repairman would never pull that hose out.

361
00:19:49,450 --> 00:19:51,050
Why is everyone acting like they've seen a ghost?

362
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:55,350
Of course.

363
00:19:55,750 --> 00:19:57,450
Lexa did something again.

364
00:19:57,480 --> 00:19:58,560
No, not Lexa.

365
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:00,650
Then who did what?

366
00:20:01,150 --> 00:20:03,650
Well, Simona, I...

367
00:20:04,050 --> 00:20:07,230
Look, it's really none of my business, right, but...

368
00:20:07,230 --> 00:20:08,730
Stop stammering and tell me what's going on.

369
00:20:11,110 --> 00:20:12,310
Lexa saw you.

370
00:20:12,310 --> 00:20:16,350
Actually, we all saw you in this kind of movie.

371
00:20:17,050 --> 00:20:18,150
In Bergman?

372
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:20,450
You'd better see for yourself.

373
00:20:20,450 --> 00:20:20,770
Let's go.

374
00:20:25,830 --> 00:20:26,670
Where are you going?

375
00:20:27,050 --> 00:20:27,930
To the attic.

376
00:20:28,950 --> 00:20:37,150
In the role of the dark huntsman, role in full.

377
00:20:46,150 --> 00:20:47,150
Come on, come on.

378
00:20:56,750 --> 00:21:00,350
So you really think your mommy would act in something like this?

379
00:21:02,630 --> 00:21:03,030
I see.

380
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:07,000
Wouldn't you rather I tell you what I saw at the movies yesterday?

381
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:08,100
Sex and the City.

382
00:21:08,180 --> 00:21:10,340
I think it could've been rated for all audiences.

383
00:21:10,340 --> 00:21:10,960
Dad, stop.

384
00:21:12,550 --> 00:21:14,550
I admit I don't pay enough attention to you.

385
00:21:15,050 --> 00:21:19,540
I last saw Lexa here on Tuesday when he came to show me at the Jezevec how nicely they embroidered him.

386
00:21:19,540 --> 00:21:20,740
That was me, Mom.

387
00:21:21,850 --> 00:21:24,350
Fine, I have seen Lexa recently too.

388
00:21:25,050 --> 00:21:27,950
I know, last Christmas wasn't great.

389
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:30,000
You had to tap beer all night.

390
00:21:30,250 --> 00:21:35,250
I also understand you'd like to have something other than yesterday's leftovers for breakfast sometimes.

391
00:21:36,150 --> 00:21:38,150
Fine, I'm not an ideal mother.

392
00:21:38,550 --> 00:21:39,550
But this?

393
00:21:40,250 --> 00:21:44,650
Not that I haven't had offers, before you ruined my figure, but I have my limits.

394
00:21:45,550 --> 00:21:46,250
Really?

395
00:21:46,950 --> 00:21:48,720
Did any of you actually watch it to the end?

396
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:49,240
Well, yeah.

397
00:21:50,050 --> 00:21:55,920
At the end, everyone meets at the lord's castle and then the dark huntsman comes, right, and pulls out his...

398
00:21:56,450 --> 00:21:57,350
Read it.

399
00:21:57,420 --> 00:21:57,940
Lexa.

400
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:03,450
So, Sasha?

401
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:04,640
1980.

402
00:22:06,250 --> 00:22:07,250
How old was I then?

403
00:22:09,250 --> 00:22:10,420
I was ten.

404
00:22:10,550 --> 00:22:13,140
Wow, but she looked older.

405
00:22:13,140 --> 00:22:13,900
Ozzak.

406
00:22:14,850 --> 00:22:18,050
So it wasn't you?

407
00:22:19,450 --> 00:22:28,950
Mom, this is great, because now, you're here with us, you notice us, and I...

408
00:22:28,950 --> 00:22:36,750
Imagine, Mom, for the first time I managed to outrun the fourth graders and they only beat me up a little, and you're listening to me, Mom.

409
00:22:39,250 --> 00:22:41,350
Easy now, easy.

410
00:22:41,750 --> 00:22:44,360
We only hug when the Jezevec has a good take.

411
00:22:44,360 --> 00:22:45,140
Thanks, Mom.

412
00:22:45,930 --> 00:22:47,910
Now I can make up for what I've missed.

413
00:22:48,690 --> 00:22:49,510
Slow down, wild one.

414
00:22:50,050 --> 00:22:52,030
I haven't seen those five porn films yet.

415
00:22:52,030 --> 00:22:52,430
Hold on.

416
00:22:53,350 --> 00:22:56,750
First check if there's nothing objectionable in those porn tapes.

417
00:22:57,650 --> 00:23:00,850
Yeah, this one's American, you can watch that right away.

418
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:12,930
And he lent it.

419
00:23:12,930 --> 00:23:15,850
This is no Cries and Whispers.

420
00:23:16,950 --> 00:23:18,250
What would it be then?

421
00:23:18,430 --> 00:23:20,430
I have absolutely no idea what to call it.

422
00:23:20,450 --> 00:23:21,970
There are completely naked people here.

423
00:23:23,450 --> 00:23:26,850
Marcelka, like I said, you have to fast-forward the boring scenes.

424
00:23:27,350 --> 00:23:28,850
But what did you think of the story?

425
00:23:29,550 --> 00:23:30,320
The story?

426
00:23:30,320 --> 00:23:30,580
Yeah.

427
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:34,620
You mean the part where three new colleagues come to the fire station?

428
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:36,300
And they call that job interviews?

429
00:23:36,420 --> 00:23:37,280
Nobody was talking there.

430
00:23:37,460 --> 00:23:38,320
Exactly.

431
00:23:38,650 --> 00:23:40,140
Short, simple, to the bone.

432
00:23:40,450 --> 00:23:41,650
So what's the problem?

433
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:44,900
Actually, there was no problem at all.

434
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:48,260
Zoran actually didn't fall asleep, and neither did I.

435
00:23:50,350 --> 00:23:51,550
He sends you this.

436
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:55,850
And I have something for you too.

437
00:23:58,650 --> 00:23:59,450
It's Bergman.

438
00:23:59,850 --> 00:24:01,070
An absolute classic.

439
00:24:01,070 --> 00:24:01,930
The Seventh Seal.

440
00:24:01,930 --> 00:24:03,370
You'll love it.

441
00:24:03,550 --> 00:24:04,850
It's in the original language.

442
00:24:05,150 --> 00:24:08,250
And now if you'll excuse me.

443
00:24:08,450 --> 00:24:11,150
I have some work in the back.

444
00:24:11,440 --> 00:24:12,080
Good night.

445
00:24:24,750 --> 00:24:26,730
Mom, well this is just great.

446
00:24:27,350 --> 00:24:28,150
Well, here we go.

447
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:29,850
You really got me in trouble.

448
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:31,060
What?

449
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:35,060
Please, can you at least tell me which of those films you were in?

450
00:24:35,060 --> 00:24:35,580
What?

451
00:24:36,750 --> 00:24:38,450
How can you not remember?

452
00:24:39,750 --> 00:24:42,750
Oh well, I'll read you the titles and you tell me, okay?

453
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:49,950
The Wizard of Oz, Hotel Wet Star, not that one, right?

454
00:24:52,950 --> 00:25:05,750
Foreskin on a Hot Tin Roof, Twelve Unfinished Men, Jesus Christ, that must've been intense, Three Loins for Cinderella.

455
00:25:06,450 --> 00:25:07,550
That one too?

456
00:25:09,450 --> 00:25:11,450
Thirty Thrusts of Major Zeman.

457
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:12,150
Yeah.

458
00:25:13,350 --> 00:25:14,950
Circus Humberto?

459
00:25:15,950 --> 00:25:18,750
Mom, how would I know if there were bears in it?
